{
  "texts": [
    "Generative AI can offer innovative solutions to these longstanding challenges by providing personalized, interactive, and adaptive learning tools [42,43].",
    "The Med-PaLM 2 model answered medical test questions on the USMLE dataset with 86.5% accuracy [44], while Chat-GPT based on GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 obtained approximately 60% and 86.1%, respectively [45,46].",
    "These findings imply that LLMs and generative AI models can generate reliable, explainable outputs, making them valuable aids in learning and clinical reasoning.",
    "As research and development in the field of generative AI continues to grow, driven by large investments from technology companies and research institutions [47], the incorporation of these advanced tools into orthopedic education is poised to revolutionize the field, enabling a more engaging, accessible, and efficient learning environment.",
    "Section 3: Performance of generative AI in orthopedic examinationsA study by Lum assessed the performance of ChatGPT in the Orthopedic In-Training Examination by analyzing its answers to 207 questions and comparing its scores with those of orthopedic surgery residents over a fiveyear period [48]."
  ]
}